{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddb35c1f5-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s352"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"352"},"text":"§ 352.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Limitation on amount of obligations of certain maturities which may be discounted and rediscounted","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System may, by regulation, limit to a percentage of the assets of a Federal reserve bank the amount of notes, drafts, acceptances, or bills having a maturity in excess of three months, but not exceeding six months, exclusive of days of grace, which may be discounted by such bank, and the amount of notes, drafts, bills, or acceptances having a maturity in excess of six months, but not exceeding nine months, which may be rediscounted by such bank.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddb35c1f6-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-12-23/ch6/s13A"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1913, ch. 6, § 13A","children":[],"tail":" (par.), formerly § 13a, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1923-03-04/ch252"},"text":"Mar. 4, 1923, ch. 252","children":[],"tail":", title IV, § 404, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/1480"},"text":"42 Stat. 1480","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-23/ch614"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1935, ch. 614","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 203(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/704"},"text":"49 Stat. 704","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 13A, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/242/tI/s142/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–242, title I, § 142(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/2281"},"text":"105 Stat. 2281","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddb35c1f7-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddb35c1f8-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddb35c1f9-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is comprised of fifth par. of section 13A, formerly section 13a, as added ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1923-03-04"},"text":"Mar. 4, 1923","children":[],"tail":". Pars. 1 to 4 of section 13A are set out as sections 348, 349 to 351 of this title, respectively."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"iddb35c1fa-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"iddb35c1fb-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 203(a) of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1935-08-23"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1935","children":[],"tail":", changed name of Federal Reserve Board to Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
